SQLite is a tiny database who cames by default with Ruby on Rails when you start a new project without pass any parameter such: "rails new PROJECT -d DATABASE-ADAPTER". Few days ago I was search a graphic tool to manage it without go to console everytime.

# SQLite Browser
When I used to code PHP for web development I had to use PHPMyAdmin or MySQL Workbench, with time I changed to Ruby on Rails and started to learn about SQLite, MongoDB, PostgreSQL(For Heroku).
With PHP I had a lot of graphical interfaces to manage my MySQL databases so I missed it when started with Rails...Making a search on SQLite official web site I found a lot of tool but anyone avaiable
to my operating system (Debian Wheezy). Making another search on my distro repositories I founded what I needed, the SQLite Browser. Its small as SQLite itself and remembered my Windows 95 :P - Its very easy to use
and interactive.
<br /><br />
![SQLite Screenshot](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
<br /><br />

# Install
To install it on Debian is easy:

{% highlight bash %}
$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install sqlitebrowser
{% endhighlight %}
<br />
# Using it
After install just use the interface to insert/delete data in your database, or create a new one.
